---
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---
<PageLayout title="Admissions">
  <div class="prose-bfs">
    <h2>Who Can Apply</h2>
    <p>
      We can consider requests for placements for children with a diagnosis of autism who also have an Education, Health and Care Plan (EHCP) and are between the ages of 5 and 16 years old.
    </p>
    <p>
      Fees are paid to Bright Futures School Limited by the Local Authority. We are not able to consider private funding.
    </p>

    <h2>Placement Request — Local Authority Pathway</h2>
    <p>
      If your child's Local Authority (LA) is considering Bright Futures School as a potential placement, they will make contact with us directly. We will then arrange for you and your child to visit the school before any decision is made.
    </p>

    <h2>Placement Request — Parent / Carer Pathway</h2>
    <p>
      If you are a parent or carer who would like to request Bright Futures School as a placement for your child, you should:
    </p>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-2 mb-4">
      <li>Contact your child's Local Authority SEND team and request that they consider Bright Futures School as a placement.</li>
      <li>Contact us directly to find out more and arrange an informal visit.</li>
      <li>Complete our First Contact Form and return it to the school office.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      <a href="/documents/First-Contact-Form.docx" class="btn-outline inline-block" download>Download First Contact Form (.docx)</a>
    </p>

    <h2>Arrange a Visit</h2>
    <p>
      We warmly welcome visits from parents, carers, and Local Authority representatives. Please <a href="/contact">contact us</a> to arrange a convenient time.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6 border border-gray-200">
    <p class="font-semibold text-brand-navy mb-1">Have more questions?</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">We've put together answers to the questions families ask us most often.</p>
    <a href="/admissions/faq" class="btn-primary">View Admissions FAQ</a>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
